Q/- What is a Spring Bean and Spring container? How to activate the Spring Container in our
    application.
    
    
    
   Spring Bean=>
                
                Any java class which is register with Spring container is known as Spring bean.
                
   
   Spring container=>
                     
                     A spring application the pure java class that control all the bean class is 
                     known as Spring container.
                     
                        
   how to active spring container
   
   Create a Spring configuration XML file (e.g., applicationContext.xml) and define your beans and their configurations within this file.
   
  => Use the ClassPathXmlApplicationContext or FileSystemXmlApplicationContext classes 
     to load the XML configuration file and initialize the Spring Container.
                                 
                
                  


